law.text:
Pursuant to § 4-602 of this subtitle, the Department shall establish and publish by October 25 each year open seasons to catch the following game and freshwater fish for the ensuing year:
Largemouth bass and smallmouth bass;
Pike and pickerel;
Walleye;
Rockfish, also known as striped bass;
Brook trout, brown trout, and rainbow trout;
American shad, hickory shad, and herring;
Suckers, catfish, carp, eel, and gudgeon;
All species of sunfish, including bluegill;
Rock bass, also known as redeye;
Fallfish;
Crappie; and
White perch and yellow perch.
